WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:02.333
Milo, where are you?

00:02.336 --> 00:03.496
ANNOUNCER:
Previously on "Slasher".

00:03.754 --> 00:04.743
[ Gasps ]
Oh, God.

00:05.047 --> 00:07.208
[ Screaming ]

00:07.508 --> 00:09.373
LISA-ANN: A series
of bloody murders...

00:09.385 --> 00:12.297
...two journalists, Dylan Bennett
and Alison Sutherland.

00:12.597 --> 00:14.963
Why don't we ask
The Executioner himself?

00:15.224 --> 00:17.431
Please talk to me.
Let me interview you.

00:18.102 --> 00:19.888
I mean, call me crazy, but
throwing yourself to the lions

00:19.896 --> 00:20.976
does seem a little prideful.

00:21.272 --> 00:22.728
[ Crickets chirping ]

00:25.067 --> 00:25.931
[ Metal door clangs ]

00:26.110 --> 00:27.486
You have no sins?

00:27.820 --> 00:28.775
No, nothing.

00:29.113 --> 00:31.525
ALISON: Ariel Peterson '5
disappearance was big news,

00:31.532 --> 00:32.908
but with no new leads

00:32.909 --> 00:34.445
the story started
to die a slow death.

00:34.452 --> 00:35.362
So...

00:35.369 --> 00:36.654
I made sure it stayed live.

00:37.413 --> 00:38.198
Benny Peterson...

00:38.414 --> 00:40.826
All the facts pointed to him,
but there was no smoking gun.

00:41.042 --> 00:41.997
So I provided one.

00:43.669 --> 00:44.579
[ Alison whimpers ]

00:44.587 --> 00:46.123
[ Alison screams ]

00:46.130 --> 00:47.711
You can't do this! No!

00:49.383 --> 00:50.338
CAM: She got in the car.

00:51.761 --> 00:52.546
Shit.

00:53.221 --> 00:55.462
GIRL: I tsy bitsy spider...

00:56.182 --> 01:00.516
Don't stop singing, Ariel.
It's beautiful.

01:03.356 --> 01:04.892
ARIEL: You're like a totally
different person

01:04.899 --> 01:06.230
when you're around your friends.

01:07.401 --> 01:08.481
You are, Larkwood.

01:08.486 --> 01:09.191
You're mean,

01:09.445 --> 01:12.152
and you're cold, and you act like
you don't care about anything.

01:12.323 --> 01:13.358
Especially me.

01:14.283 --> 01:15.068
No!

01:15.326 --> 01:17.658
No, just stay there.
I don't want to see you right now.

01:18.871 --> 01:19.826
[ Sniffling ]

01:19.830 --> 01:21.491
Yeah, have fun
at your party, asshole!

01:22.291 --> 01:23.201
[ Turns off phone ]

01:23.209 --> 01:24.699
[ Continues sniffling ]

01:25.419 --> 01:27.284
[ Retches ]

01:27.547 --> 01:29.253
[Coughing ]

01:32.468 --> 01:33.457
[ Retches ]

01:33.678 --> 01:34.508
[ Ambulance stops ]

01:34.971 --> 01:37.303
Ah, looks like somebody
just yawned a big, bright,

01:37.306 --> 01:38.170
chunky rainbow.

01:38.432 --> 01:40.047
Looks like the Peterson girl.

01:40.810 --> 01:41.595
You okay, hun?

01:42.603 --> 01:43.558
TRENT: Can you walk?

01:44.939 --> 01:46.395
-I think so.
-TRENT: Yeah?

01:46.691 --> 01:47.897
All right, here's
what you're gonna do.

01:48.609 --> 01:49.564
You're gonna go straight home,

01:49.902 --> 01:51.142
you're gonna drink
a bucket of water,

01:51.153 --> 01:53.064
and take two aspirin,
and jump into bed.

01:54.740 --> 01:57.277
Not gonna die.
You'll just think you did.

01:57.868 --> 02:00.325
Shouldn't we drive her home
or take her to emerg...?

02:00.580 --> 02:02.912
Hold her hand for three hours,
until she sobers up?

02:03.165 --> 02:04.496
-[ Retches ]
-TRENT: Let her walk it off.

02:05.042 --> 02:05.872
Hey...

02:06.502 --> 02:08.413
if you want me kept up all night,
June bug,

02:09.297 --> 02:10.662
it's gonna be because of you.

02:10.673 --> 02:12.254
[ Engine running ]

02:12.717 --> 02:13.627
She'll be fine.

02:14.302 --> 02:15.883
She'll be fine.

02:18.973 --> 02:19.758
No.

02:20.224 --> 02:20.974
Wait!

02:21.392 --> 02:22.222
Come back!

02:25.938 --> 02:26.723
[ Whimpers ]

02:37.450 --> 02:39.315
VAUGHN: You're Ariel, right?

02:41.996 --> 02:43.156
You been drinkin'?

02:43.956 --> 02:44.741
No.

02:45.541 --> 02:46.906
VAUGHN: That's all right.
I'm off-duty.

02:47.752 --> 02:49.788
I don't care how many
shots of Jager you did

02:49.795 --> 02:51.251
or with who.

02:51.631 --> 02:53.713
I just wanna make sure
you get home safe and sound.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.084
[ Crickets chirping ]

02:55.468 --> 02:57.083
Go on. Get in.

02:57.595 --> 02:59.085
I'll drive you home.

02:59.555 --> 03:00.965
Thank you.

03:01.641 --> 03:02.471
[ Sighs ]

03:25.539 --> 03:26.745
So where are all your friends?

03:28.751 --> 03:29.957
At a party.

03:31.003 --> 03:32.709
VAUGHN: Why aren't you?

03:34.048 --> 03:35.128
Ah!

03:36.634 --> 03:38.340
Boy troubles, huh?

03:38.511 --> 03:39.375
I got it.

03:40.096 --> 03:41.051
How'd you know?

03:41.722 --> 03:43.508
Well, for starters,
you've been crying.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.465
-VAUGHN: Drank far too much.
-[ Snickers ]

03:46.852 --> 03:49.264
And you're wandering
around Waterbury at half past 11.

03:49.522 --> 03:50.307
[ Ariel chuckles ]

03:55.861 --> 03:58.022
Oh, we just live off
of Greenwood.

03:58.197 --> 04:01.030
Yeah, I figured you might
wanna sober up some.

04:01.033 --> 04:03.194
Unless, of course, your parents
are cool with you drinking.

04:04.245 --> 04:06.827
-No.
-VAUGHN: I didn't think so.

04:08.499 --> 04:10.785
I've been there, Ariel.

04:11.877 --> 04:15.961
I had the girl of my dreams and...

04:16.507 --> 04:17.462
...I lost her.

04:18.759 --> 04:20.169
What happened?

04:23.139 --> 04:25.505
Connie Renn was her name.

04:26.559 --> 04:29.050
Smart, quiet...

04:29.061 --> 04:30.267
Beautiful.

04:31.063 --> 04:33.099
Different, you know?

04:34.608 --> 04:36.018
Unique.

04:37.903 --> 04:39.018
A lot like you.

04:39.321 --> 04:40.401
[ Chuckles ]

04:41.782 --> 04:44.899
VAUGHN: That was...
That was 20 years ago.

04:46.162 --> 04:49.825
Life just... life just goes on.

05:03.471 --> 05:06.838
It's really easy
talking to you, Ariel.

05:07.850 --> 05:08.885
You, too.

05:14.732 --> 05:16.268
You, uh...

05:17.943 --> 05:20.104
...you know I meant
what I said.

05:20.696 --> 05:22.778
You remind me of Connie.

05:26.827 --> 05:27.612
[ Laughs ]

05:27.995 --> 05:30.577
I'm-- I'm just
like your boyfriend.

05:30.581 --> 05:33.118
[ Laughs]
I'm just a... a total... idiot.

05:33.292 --> 05:35.078
-[ Laughs ]
-No! Don't say that.

05:35.586 --> 05:37.042
You're like a hero.

05:39.924 --> 05:41.334
Yeah?

05:42.843 --> 05:44.344
[ Snickers ]

05:55.314 --> 05:57.896
[ Crickets chirping ]

06:01.403 --> 06:03.940
[ Sighs ]

06:07.409 --> 06:08.444
You think I'm a hero?

06:09.954 --> 06:11.285
Yeah.

06:25.970 --> 06:28.586
Do you know why girls
date older guys?

06:30.558 --> 06:32.219
It's because you mature
so much faster.

06:32.393 --> 06:33.849
I mean, you just leave us
right in the dust.

06:34.979 --> 06:37.391
I can just walk the rest
of the way home, if that's easier.

06:37.857 --> 06:39.017
No, no, no. Come on.
It's okay.

06:39.191 --> 06:40.351
-[ Panting ]
-It's okay.

06:40.568 --> 06:41.853
-Ariel.
-Please.

06:42.027 --> 06:44.188
-Please, I just wanna go home!
-It's okay.

06:44.363 --> 06:45.978
It's okay. Shh. Shh.

06:45.990 --> 06:47.150
Please, just let me go
home now.

06:47.157 --> 06:47.691
[ Sobbing ]

06:47.867 --> 06:49.403
No! Please, no!

06:49.910 --> 06:50.695
No!

06:50.911 --> 06:51.775
-No!
-It's okay.

06:52.079 --> 06:53.159
-No!
-All right!

06:53.163 --> 06:54.073
-No! No!
-Stop!

06:54.623 --> 06:55.874
-ARIEL: No!
-VAUGHN: It's okay!

06:56.041 --> 06:56.996
-ARIEL: No!
-VAUGHN: Stop.

06:57.251 --> 06:58.832
-ARIEL: N0!
-VAUGHN: Shh. Shh.

06:59.253 --> 07:02.040
-ARIEL: Please, help!
-VAUGHN: Stay calm. Stay calm.

07:02.840 --> 07:03.625
ARIEL: Stop!

07:04.049 --> 07:05.585
[ Screaming ]

07:05.593 --> 07:06.423
ARIEL: No!

07:20.941 --> 07:21.976
[ Sighs ]

07:35.915 --> 07:36.700
Hey.

07:36.916 --> 07:38.497
Hey, hey, hey.

07:38.500 --> 07:40.286
-Come back here.
-Jake needs breakfast.

07:40.461 --> 07:43.453
Jake is asleep.

07:44.548 --> 07:46.209
[ Sighs ]

07:47.259 --> 07:48.123
[ Continued sighs ]

07:48.510 --> 07:50.046
I could do this all day.

07:52.640 --> 07:55.052
Lying here with you.

07:55.059 --> 07:57.266
[ Sniffs ]
It's like heaven.

08:10.157 --> 08:12.239
I think this is good.

08:14.954 --> 08:17.115
Imagine if we had
a real life together?

08:17.915 --> 08:19.371
You...

08:19.375 --> 08:21.286
me... and Jake.

08:22.753 --> 08:24.118
And Nancy.

08:26.465 --> 08:28.706
You guys have always
wanted kids.

08:32.680 --> 08:34.341
Could be like this every day.

08:40.270 --> 08:41.476
Gonna be late for work.

08:49.530 --> 08:50.315
[ Sighs ]

08:50.990 --> 08:52.730
You know, when you talk
like this, Ariel...

08:54.410 --> 08:56.696
All you do is make me
really upset.

08:57.913 --> 08:59.528
[ Sighs ]

09:00.749 --> 09:02.285
[ Door opening, closing ]

09:03.711 --> 09:05.326
Is Daddy mad at me?

09:06.380 --> 09:08.462
[ Door being locked ]

09:09.758 --> 09:12.295
No, honey, of course not.

09:12.678 --> 09:14.088
Just go back to sleep.

10:17.034 --> 10:17.989
Poor Alison, huh?

10:18.494 --> 10:19.904
From the frying pan
into the fire.

10:21.663 --> 10:23.870
Are you enjoying this, Dylan?

10:24.625 --> 10:26.331
Half the town
is getting sliced and diced.

10:26.335 --> 10:28.291
No. I'm not enjoying this.

10:29.671 --> 10:31.457
Still.

10:31.465 --> 10:33.376
You know, it's worked out
kinda well for you.

10:34.384 --> 10:36.170
Alison's dead,
and you're in charge.

10:36.386 --> 10:37.375
I'm not in charge.

10:37.387 --> 10:39.764
Sarah, I'm just trying to keep
this thing a float here.

10:39.765 --> 10:41.926
[ Birds chirping ]

10:41.934 --> 10:43.219
It's kinda sounding
like an accusation.

10:43.852 --> 10:45.058
No.

10:45.312 --> 10:47.803
No, a-- an accusation
would be me...

10:48.232 --> 10:50.018
asking you where you were...

10:50.692 --> 10:52.557
when Alison was murdered.
'Cause...

10:54.154 --> 10:55.143
...you weren't here.

10:55.697 --> 10:56.823
Right, a journalist

10:57.199 --> 11:00.111
killing an entire town,
to put himself on the map.

11:01.495 --> 11:03.451
It's a juicy story, isn't it?

11:06.708 --> 11:08.494
You're unbelievable.

11:20.973 --> 11:23.259
Well, you wasted no time
moving in.

11:23.684 --> 11:24.844
Someone's gotta
hold down the fort.

11:25.978 --> 11:26.763
Dylan...

11:27.354 --> 11:29.936
this story is breaking... Big!

11:30.232 --> 11:31.893
And I wanna talk next steps.

11:33.360 --> 11:34.395
So does Megyn Kelly.

11:34.570 --> 11:35.400
[ Clears throat ]

11:35.988 --> 11:39.196
And Dateline
and 48 Hours Mystery.

11:40.242 --> 11:42.779
Well, lucky for me,
I got in on the ground floor.

11:43.370 --> 11:44.701
What are you doing tonight
for dinner?

11:44.913 --> 11:47.199
Eating a sandwich, right here.

11:47.541 --> 11:50.157
You can take an hour out
and have dinner with me,

11:50.419 --> 11:52.501
like a civilized person.

11:54.548 --> 11:55.958
Tell me the time and the place.

11:59.344 --> 12:02.177
Well, there is only one place.
How's, um, how's seven?

12:03.015 --> 12:03.800
Perfect.

12:04.099 --> 12:05.134
Looking forward to it.

12:05.434 --> 12:06.469
[ Phone ringing ]

12:17.279 --> 12:20.146
[ Birds chirping ]

12:20.699 --> 12:22.781
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:30.042 --> 12:31.532
Hey.

12:31.710 --> 12:32.950
Can I come in?

12:35.380 --> 12:36.335
What do ya want?

12:36.632 --> 12:38.418
Look, I'm not here to fight,
or upset you,

12:38.425 --> 12:39.540
or make anything worse.

12:39.551 --> 12:42.167
But I think I found something out
about Ariel.

12:43.555 --> 12:44.965
Come on in.

12:45.891 --> 12:47.301
Everything in this case
has led directly back

12:48.310 --> 12:49.390
You see, not anymore, though.

12:49.603 --> 12:51.639
Marjorie Travers gave an interview
to the Bulletin,

12:51.647 --> 12:55.310
where she says that she saw Ariel
on Tecumseh Street at 11:30.

12:55.317 --> 12:57.774
Which makes her the last person
to see Ariel alive.

12:59.863 --> 13:00.613
Okay.

13:01.198 --> 13:03.530
We now know that June and Trent
saw her seven minutes later

13:03.533 --> 13:05.148
on Chariton Street.

13:05.452 --> 13:06.783
Nah, that's impossible.

13:07.621 --> 13:09.737
Chariton's like at least
a 20-minute walk away.

13:09.915 --> 13:10.700
SARAH: Exactly.

13:10.958 --> 13:12.539
So either Ariel was
in two places at once,

13:12.542 --> 13:14.078
or Majorie is lying...

13:14.795 --> 13:15.784
about everything.

13:21.260 --> 13:22.545
[ Cars driving past ]

13:22.761 --> 13:23.546
[ Shudder ]

13:23.804 --> 13:27.388
I saw Ariel where I saw her
and when I saw her.

13:30.560 --> 13:32.596
Benny Peterson was
at the Legion that night.

13:32.938 --> 13:35.850
That's right around the corner
from where you said you saw Ariel.

13:35.857 --> 13:37.597
Yeah, I know where the Legion is.

13:40.904 --> 13:42.610
He left at 11:40 p.m.

13:42.781 --> 13:44.772
And no one saw him again
until the next morning.

13:45.200 --> 13:48.613
That's because he was busy raping
and murdering his daughter.

13:48.912 --> 13:51.153
CAM: Well, we now know
that's impossible.

13:52.708 --> 13:54.664
So I'm gonna ask you again,
Marjorie.

13:55.711 --> 13:59.750
Are you sure... that's Ariel
that you saw that night?

14:02.968 --> 14:04.504
I was havin' a smoke,

14:05.304 --> 14:07.761
in front
of the White Onion Tavern.

14:08.849 --> 14:11.090
Ariel Peterson walked by me.

14:11.643 --> 14:14.259
I know it was 11:30 'cause...

14:14.730 --> 14:19.269
Karaoke Night at the Onion
had just... let out.

14:20.402 --> 14:23.485
Starts 9:30, goes two hours.

14:24.489 --> 14:26.696
Unless my math is wrong.

14:27.993 --> 14:30.359
That'd put it at 11:30 p.m.

14:33.498 --> 14:37.537
Well, thank you very much
for your time, Marjorie.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.581
Let's go.

14:42.174 --> 14:43.084
You know,

14:43.091 --> 14:45.673
that someone like you gets
to live and waste their life

14:45.677 --> 14:47.838
is wrong on so many levels.

14:48.972 --> 14:49.722
Sweetheart...

14:52.100 --> 14:54.261
Your mother might've been
a whore,

14:54.644 --> 14:56.896
but at least she was fun.

14:57.314 --> 14:58.099
[ Snickers ]

14:58.398 --> 15:00.309
Uh, just...

15:01.610 --> 15:03.692
Stay classy, Marjorie.

15:11.036 --> 15:11.866
[ Birds chirping ]

15:12.120 --> 15:13.985
SARAH: I saw Ariel walk by.
Blah, blah, blah.

15:13.997 --> 15:14.986
She didn't see her.

15:15.207 --> 15:17.118
She's unbelievable.
I know, it's upsetting.

15:17.334 --> 15:18.119
Upsetting?

15:18.585 --> 15:22.749
Cam, she was 15. Okay?
She was a child.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.042
And I think how terrified
she must've been.

15:25.592 --> 15:28.834
I know, but, honestly,
it's not your concern.

15:30.222 --> 15:32.133
Sarah, you didn't even know Ariel.

15:32.808 --> 15:34.218
I'm
5
o
rry
7

15:35.936 --> 15:38.643
Alison, Trent... June?

15:40.232 --> 15:41.768
The Executioner targeted them.

15:42.192 --> 15:45.184
Killed them because
of their association with this girl.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.532
When I think about what
she must've gone through...

15:49.533 --> 15:50.443
[ Chuckles ]

15:50.450 --> 15:51.781
It almost makes me wonder
where The Executioner

15:51.785 --> 15:53.776
is actually doing God's work.

15:54.162 --> 15:55.618
What?

15:58.083 --> 15:59.493
Marjorie's lying.

16:00.669 --> 16:02.409
You know it, and I know it.

16:04.005 --> 16:05.256
No.

16:07.175 --> 16:08.005
Hey...

16:08.593 --> 16:09.924
The other day...

16:10.679 --> 16:12.715
Those things,
all that shit I said...

16:15.183 --> 16:16.434
I'm sorry.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.052
It's okay. Really, I'm sorry, too.

16:20.230 --> 16:21.470
No.

16:21.815 --> 16:23.476
No, you being here...

16:24.359 --> 16:26.816
That's the one good thing
that's happened this summer.

16:29.698 --> 16:32.360
Okay, so, what's this one called?

16:32.617 --> 16:33.902
-A poodle!
-Good.

16:34.119 --> 16:35.325
And... this one?

16:35.620 --> 16:36.826
I like the poodle better.

16:37.080 --> 16:39.366
Well, that wasn't the question,
little man.

16:40.083 --> 16:41.948
Why do we have to
learn about this?

16:42.669 --> 16:43.954
Why? You love dogs.

16:44.337 --> 16:47.249
I do, but they're out there,
and we're in here.

16:47.799 --> 16:50.085
[ Door unlocking ]

16:52.012 --> 16:53.001
Daddy!

16:53.472 --> 16:54.257
Hey.

16:54.473 --> 16:56.213
[ Panting ]

16:56.516 --> 16:58.222
VAUGHN: Hey, how are you, buddy?

16:58.810 --> 16:59.799
You doing your lessons?

16:59.811 --> 17:00.721
Yeah.

17:00.729 --> 17:01.639
Fun fact:

17:01.646 --> 17:03.386
Did you know
that poodle's don't shed,

17:03.732 --> 17:04.767
they have to get a haircut?

17:05.025 --> 17:06.105
I didn't know that.

17:06.109 --> 17:08.191
You know what?
I got bit by a poodle once.

17:08.403 --> 17:10.189
Right there, you can feel the--
[ Growls ]

17:10.447 --> 17:11.357
[ Laughs ]

17:11.364 --> 17:13.070
Listen, buddy, I'm gonna
put this away, okay?

17:13.074 --> 17:14.814
And then you can tell me
all about poodles later.

17:14.993 --> 17:16.358
-Okay, can't wait.
-All right.

17:19.915 --> 17:21.701
[ Clears throat ]
Yeah.

17:27.547 --> 17:30.505
Earlier, I upset you...

17:30.800 --> 17:31.789
and I'm sorry.

17:38.308 --> 17:39.764
[ Snickers ]

17:40.018 --> 17:41.303
That's okay.

17:43.104 --> 17:44.605
[ Sighs ]

17:45.357 --> 17:47.564
It's okay. It's okay.

17:50.362 --> 17:51.818
[ Sighs ]

17:54.282 --> 17:55.397
It's just that...

17:56.117 --> 17:58.654
Jake started asking questions
about the world.

17:59.287 --> 18:00.447
And...

18:00.664 --> 18:01.995
I don't know what to tell him.

18:03.083 --> 18:05.745
You know, he's lived his entire life
down here.

18:06.711 --> 18:09.168
He's never played
with any other kids.

18:10.382 --> 18:13.465
-He needs to go to a real school.
-And how exactly do we do that?

18:13.468 --> 18:15.049
Ariel? Hm?

18:16.471 --> 18:19.429
You just...
you open that door and...

18:19.641 --> 18:20.721
And what do we tell everyone?

18:20.725 --> 18:22.681
Whatever you want me to say,
I'll say it.

18:22.686 --> 18:23.892
Whatever you want.

18:26.189 --> 18:28.180
That's the thing, Ariel.

18:28.817 --> 18:30.853
There's nothing we can say.

18:31.861 --> 18:34.238
They're out of the fruit roll
thingies that Jake likes.

18:34.739 --> 18:37.401
I'll get them the next time
I go to the store.

18:38.159 --> 18:38.909
[ Sighs ]

18:40.078 --> 18:41.113
We're gonna die in here.

18:41.288 --> 18:42.619
Oh, and, um,

18:42.622 --> 18:45.034
if you want anything,
just write it down.

18:45.041 --> 18:46.201
I got a mind like a sieve lately.

18:46.710 --> 18:48.166
I can't remember anything.

18:49.254 --> 18:50.334
Give me your keys.

18:51.298 --> 18:52.162
All right. All right.

18:52.340 --> 18:53.876
Here we are. Just...
take it easy.

18:54.384 --> 18:55.624
Give me your keys!

18:55.885 --> 18:56.840
VAUGHN: All right. All right.

18:57.929 --> 18:59.590
They're in my pocket, okay?

19:02.225 --> 19:03.214
Just take it easy.

19:03.602 --> 19:05.092
[ Panting ]

19:11.026 --> 19:11.811
Jake.

19:12.277 --> 19:13.232
Go stand by the door.

19:13.653 --> 19:14.517
Mommy?

19:14.863 --> 19:16.569
Honey, just do what I say.

19:17.365 --> 19:18.275
[ Panting ]

19:18.283 --> 19:20.615
You really think you're gonna have
enough time to get away, Ariel? Huh?

19:21.786 --> 19:22.616
Where you gonna go?

19:23.038 --> 19:24.528
Who you gonna stay with, Ariel?

19:25.165 --> 19:26.245
-[ Groans]
-Daddy!

19:30.337 --> 19:31.167
VAUGHN: Ariel!

19:31.379 --> 19:32.334
Okay. Okay, come on.

19:33.757 --> 19:34.837
Just keep running, baby.

19:43.850 --> 19:44.714
VAUGHN: Ariel!

19:48.188 --> 19:49.428
No.

19:49.439 --> 19:50.349
No!

19:50.357 --> 19:51.221
VAUGHN: Ariel!

19:57.656 --> 19:58.441
Jake.

19:58.782 --> 19:59.567
Daddy!

20:00.700 --> 20:01.735
Jake!

20:02.577 --> 20:03.362
Hey!

20:05.163 --> 20:05.993
ARIEL: Let him go!

20:06.539 --> 20:07.324
Let him go!

20:07.957 --> 20:08.912
Get downstairs.

20:09.584 --> 20:10.539
I won't.

20:10.543 --> 20:11.453
[ Shuddering ]

20:13.797 --> 20:15.128
Hey, buddy.

20:15.507 --> 20:17.543
Wow.
[ Chuckles ]

20:17.967 --> 20:18.752
Wow.

20:19.636 --> 20:21.046
You're getting so big.

20:23.098 --> 20:24.178
You're getting too big...

20:26.351 --> 20:29.309
You're getting too big...
for your Dad to lug around.

20:29.771 --> 20:30.726
What are you doing?

20:31.731 --> 20:33.642
I'm not going to jail, Ariel.

20:34.025 --> 20:35.981
-I'd rather die.
-No, Iain. Please, just stop.

20:36.361 --> 20:37.146
And if I die...

20:37.487 --> 20:39.193
Iain, Iain, Iain, stop!

20:39.531 --> 20:41.692
-Get downstairs now!
-Okay. Okay, okay.

20:42.617 --> 20:44.073
[ Sobbing ]
Okay, okay, okay.

20:44.452 --> 20:45.612
Let him go. Let him go.

20:45.620 --> 20:47.861
Jake. Jake, it's okay.

20:48.373 --> 20:49.909
[ Sobbing ]

20:50.333 --> 20:51.083
Please!

20:51.459 --> 20:52.744
VAUGHN: Come on, buddy.
Go on downstairs.

20:52.752 --> 20:53.582
Help us! Please!

20:54.087 --> 20:55.623
ARIEL: Help us! Please!

20:56.214 --> 20:56.964
ARIEL: Please!

20:58.133 --> 20:58.918
Help us!

20:59.134 --> 21:00.249
-VAUGHN: Come on!
-ARIEL: Help us!

21:00.510 --> 21:01.795
ARIEL: Help us!

21:06.850 --> 21:09.432
Look, all I did was ask a witness
a few questions.

21:09.436 --> 21:11.802
Without floating it by me first!

21:11.813 --> 21:12.677
Yeah, well I tried.

21:13.022 --> 21:14.558
And you weren't here. And you
weren't answering your phone.

21:14.816 --> 21:16.397
Well, I would've said no.

21:21.740 --> 21:23.071
What did Marjorie say?

21:23.616 --> 21:25.322
Did you come up with anything new?

21:26.077 --> 21:26.907
No.

21:27.120 --> 21:28.280
The same old bullshit.

21:28.580 --> 21:30.036
But this time her facts
don't line up.

21:30.039 --> 21:31.495
And we tried pressing her.

21:34.002 --> 21:34.991
We?

21:36.254 --> 21:37.460
[ Scoffs ]

21:38.965 --> 21:41.877
Jesus Christ, Cam, you just
buried your wife a week ago.

21:43.052 --> 21:45.088
You're gonna wanna watch
what you're saying, sir.

21:45.096 --> 21:47.052
And you're gonna wanna stop
thinking with your dick

21:47.056 --> 21:48.432
and start thinking like a cop!

21:48.600 --> 21:50.306
And until you can,
I want you to go home!

21:50.477 --> 21:54.140
CAM: Look, whoever took Ariel
is a target now.

21:54.147 --> 21:55.136
The same way June was.

21:55.482 --> 21:57.018
That's my concern!

21:58.151 --> 21:59.857
I want you to go home.

22:00.195 --> 22:02.106
I want you to go home, Cam! Now!

22:03.656 --> 22:04.987
Sir.

22:06.075 --> 22:07.656
[ Door opening ]

22:08.745 --> 22:10.235
[ Door closing ]

22:17.212 --> 22:18.748
[ Hits desk ]

22:28.723 --> 22:30.338
[ Restaurant chatter ]

22:32.977 --> 22:34.387
What are you gonna have?

22:35.063 --> 22:38.351
Well, it's a toss up between
the 0550 Bucco potato stack

22:38.608 --> 22:42.772
and the Chinese chicken salad
with Mandarin staples.

22:42.779 --> 22:44.269
Welcome to 1996.

22:44.656 --> 22:45.486
[ Giggles]

22:46.699 --> 22:47.529
Cheers.

22:49.327 --> 22:50.567
To what?

22:51.037 --> 22:52.993
The biggest story
since Casey Anthony.

22:52.997 --> 22:55.534
Yeah, well, I'm not sure everyone
shares your enthusiasm.

22:57.043 --> 22:58.328
Okay.

22:59.504 --> 23:01.620
I think there's been a bit
of a misunderstanding.

23:01.923 --> 23:02.833
No.

23:03.049 --> 23:06.132
No misunderstanding.
You chose Alison over me.

23:06.886 --> 23:08.592
But then she got her head
deep-fried.

23:10.139 --> 23:11.049
Okay.

23:11.057 --> 23:12.763
So, then,
how do I make it better?

23:14.644 --> 23:15.975
What are you offering?

23:16.145 --> 23:17.134
What do you want?

23:17.689 --> 23:19.054
More money?

23:19.232 --> 23:20.017
Done.

23:20.275 --> 23:21.310
Airtime?

23:21.776 --> 23:23.937
You'll be my go-to guy
on this case.

23:24.571 --> 23:27.358
We can talk about bringing you in
on a permanent basis.

23:29.409 --> 23:31.491
Why don't you come by my hotel?

23:32.203 --> 23:33.864
We'll order a bottle.

23:34.539 --> 23:37.201
-Do a little career planning.
-A book deal.

23:39.377 --> 23:40.662
I'm sorry. What?

23:42.422 --> 23:43.832
A book deal.

23:44.507 --> 23:45.747
True crime.

23:46.092 --> 23:48.549
All of the killings
started 30 years ago.

23:48.970 --> 23:49.755
[ Scoffs ]

23:50.054 --> 23:52.796
-I'm not a publisher, Dylan.
-You've published four books.

23:53.433 --> 23:54.843
And you didn't write any of 'em.

24:00.690 --> 24:03.557
You ready to order?
'Cause I know what I want.

24:06.279 --> 24:07.394
[ Buzzing ]

24:08.281 --> 24:10.112
[ Door opening ]

24:12.410 --> 24:14.366
Sarah. This is unexpected.

24:14.537 --> 24:15.526
You're not my father.

24:17.749 --> 24:21.241
You may think you are or you may
wanna think you are, but you're not.

24:21.419 --> 24:22.625
Sarah, it's not a matter
of thinking.

24:22.629 --> 24:23.709
You know, if you honestly think

24:23.713 --> 24:25.044
I'm gonna start spending
every Father's Day with you,

24:25.048 --> 24:25.958
you're insane.

24:25.965 --> 24:27.626
You are my daughter.

24:29.719 --> 24:30.834
No.

24:32.347 --> 24:33.837
No, it's impossible.

24:34.849 --> 24:36.055
And this...

24:36.684 --> 24:37.673
This is not healthy.

24:37.852 --> 24:39.843
-Can we talk about this?
-Good-bye, Tom.

24:40.021 --> 24:41.511
Sarah, please.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.250
[ Knocking at the door ]

25:09.634 --> 25:12.091
[ TV chatter ]

25:13.221 --> 25:14.757
[ Knocking continues ]

25:15.014 --> 25:16.800
Hold on.

25:19.769 --> 25:20.554
Oh!

25:20.728 --> 25:21.638
Hey!

25:21.646 --> 25:23.637
In the mood for some company?

25:25.400 --> 25:27.061
Get you a drink?

25:34.325 --> 25:35.735
Cheers.

25:40.039 --> 25:41.700
[ Exhales ]

25:46.337 --> 25:48.168
This job's gonna be
the death of you.

25:48.172 --> 25:49.378
Yeah.

25:50.883 --> 25:52.623
[ Exhales ]

25:55.346 --> 25:56.256
What's this?

25:56.764 --> 25:57.549
Oh!

25:57.849 --> 25:59.089
That's nothin'.

26:01.644 --> 26:02.884
Cut myself shaving.

26:03.813 --> 26:05.178
With a machete?

26:05.398 --> 26:07.059
[ Both laughing ]

26:13.156 --> 26:14.692
I, uh...

26:15.658 --> 26:18.149
I hear Cam
paid you a visit today.

26:18.411 --> 26:19.241
Oh.

26:19.620 --> 26:20.871
Him and that Bennett girl.

26:21.039 --> 26:23.826
Yeah, doesn't she think
she's all that.

26:24.000 --> 26:25.331
Yeah.

26:25.585 --> 26:27.701
[ Sighs ]
MARJORIE: Pretty thing, though.

26:34.010 --> 26:35.045
Her mother was, too.

26:35.595 --> 26:36.755
[ Sniffs ]

26:37.889 --> 26:40.175
That's why we hated each other.

26:40.391 --> 26:41.176
VAUGHN: Hm.

26:45.313 --> 26:46.519
What did you tell 'em?

26:47.398 --> 26:48.934
What I've always told anyone...

26:49.108 --> 26:50.939
who's asked about that night.

26:53.029 --> 26:54.018
[ Sighs ]

26:56.699 --> 26:59.441
Don't worry. It's okay.

27:06.542 --> 27:07.793
[ Sighs ]

27:12.381 --> 27:15.088
Things can get complicated,
Marjorie.

27:16.302 --> 27:17.838
You got caught in a lie.

27:18.304 --> 27:20.044
I saw what I saw.

27:20.306 --> 27:21.921
[ Snickers ]

27:22.141 --> 27:24.177
I stick to my story.

27:24.894 --> 27:27.681
Yeah, well, they're gonna be looking
for inconsistencies in your story,

27:27.688 --> 27:29.474
and there gonna try
and trick you.

27:29.732 --> 27:30.767
They?
[Laughs]

27:31.609 --> 27:34.772
I mean, it's your investigation,
right?

27:35.822 --> 27:37.062
[ Sighs ]

27:37.365 --> 27:39.230
May not stay that way.

27:41.786 --> 27:44.448
Well, don't worry,
because you know what?

27:44.872 --> 27:47.579
I am a very, very good liar.

27:49.252 --> 27:51.618
And I'm a lot smarter than I look.

27:54.966 --> 27:57.082
What was Ariel wearing that night?

27:59.345 --> 28:00.630
I-- I don't know.

28:00.930 --> 28:01.760
[ Laughs ]

28:02.306 --> 28:03.512
What was she wearing?
[ Laughs ]

28:03.891 --> 28:05.176
ReaHy?

28:05.852 --> 28:07.513
You remember what time
Karaoke was over,

28:07.520 --> 28:08.475
but you don't remember that?

28:09.188 --> 28:11.053
Which way was she walking?
North or South?

28:11.774 --> 28:12.763
Or was she running?

28:13.067 --> 28:15.103
She probably was running because
she ended up on Chariton Street

28:15.111 --> 28:15.896
seven minutes later.

28:16.070 --> 28:17.105
Oh. Look. Look. Just...

28:17.697 --> 28:20.154
Just tell me what you
want me to say...

28:20.741 --> 28:22.948
and I'll say it!

28:25.538 --> 28:27.244
I'll say it.

28:31.294 --> 28:32.659
[ Scoffs ]

28:33.754 --> 28:35.164
Okay.

28:43.806 --> 28:45.888
I got you a present.

28:46.851 --> 28:49.388
[ Gasps ]
I love presents.

28:53.232 --> 28:56.474
I nicked that off some asshole.

28:57.111 --> 28:59.067
Caught him with his pants down
at the cruising spot

28:59.071 --> 29:00.231
at the brickworks.

29:00.448 --> 29:01.813
[ Sniffs ]
Is it good?

29:02.700 --> 29:04.110
Only the best for you, baby.

29:04.327 --> 29:05.692
Oh.

29:31.729 --> 29:32.479
[ Moans]

29:34.857 --> 29:36.563
[ Breathing deeply ]

29:38.527 --> 29:40.438
[ Moans]

29:41.405 --> 29:42.906
Oh.

29:46.244 --> 29:48.405
Aw, shit, it's amazing.

29:49.080 --> 29:50.365
Oh!

29:50.998 --> 29:52.408
You're so good to me.

29:54.752 --> 29:55.616
[ Crying ]

29:55.795 --> 29:57.285
MARJORIE:
Better than all the other...

29:57.838 --> 29:59.999
people in this shithole.

30:00.341 --> 30:01.126
[ Moans]

30:01.884 --> 30:03.499
That's a good thing, girl.

30:04.971 --> 30:05.835
[ Sniffling ]

30:08.975 --> 30:10.511
I...

30:13.980 --> 30:14.765
Iain.

30:15.189 --> 30:17.396
[ Mumbling ]

30:19.986 --> 30:20.771
It's...

30:21.445 --> 30:22.275
It's hella...

30:22.655 --> 30:24.816
It's really strong.

30:25.825 --> 30:27.031
Did you?

30:28.661 --> 30:29.946
Iain?

30:32.498 --> 30:33.533
What did you do?

30:34.125 --> 30:36.207
What have you done?

30:38.421 --> 30:39.831
[ Moans]

30:41.340 --> 30:42.796
[ Sobbing ]

30:48.514 --> 30:50.880
[Yelling ]

30:51.851 --> 30:53.091
[ Sobbing ]

31:03.946 --> 31:06.528
[ Breathing deeply ]

31:53.788 --> 31:55.324
[ Sniffs ]

32:07.676 --> 32:09.086
Hey, preacher.

32:10.596 --> 32:11.551
Done with that?

32:11.972 --> 32:12.722
Thanks.

32:12.973 --> 32:15.134
Please give that back.

32:15.142 --> 32:16.302
A little light reading, huh?

32:16.560 --> 32:17.390
What is it today?

32:17.686 --> 32:19.677
Hand it back... now!

32:20.147 --> 32:21.648
Blah, blah, blah.

32:25.528 --> 32:27.143
[ Prisoners cheering ]

32:27.822 --> 32:28.777
[ Groaning ]

32:30.116 --> 32:31.652
[ Screaming ]

32:38.499 --> 32:39.284
[ Groans]

32:50.052 --> 32:53.294
[ Police radio chatter ]

33:06.026 --> 33:07.732
[ Sighs ]

33:09.655 --> 33:11.236
Marjorie Travers
has been shooting smack

33:11.240 --> 33:13.151
since I was in little league.

33:15.369 --> 33:18.782
I say we run the syringe for prints
and do a sweep of the room.

33:20.249 --> 33:22.956
Even long-time users
make mistakes, Cam.

33:23.252 --> 33:24.742
She probably got a hot load.

33:25.671 --> 33:26.751
Yeah.

33:27.298 --> 33:29.084
Maybe that's what this is.

33:30.342 --> 33:31.923
Maybe it isn't.

33:42.062 --> 33:42.812
[ Sighs ]

33:44.023 --> 33:45.854
[ Crickets chirping ]

33:46.567 --> 33:47.852
And you're positive
it's Marjorie Travers?

33:48.068 --> 33:49.057
-MAN ON PHONE: Mm-hm.
-100?

33:49.236 --> 33:50.521
MAN ON PHONE: Yeah,
we got the confirmation.

33:50.529 --> 33:51.314
I t's definitely her.

33:51.489 --> 33:53.445
Yep, okay. Thank you.

33:55.784 --> 33:57.399
They're saying it's an overdose.

33:57.411 --> 33:58.446
How convenient.

33:58.454 --> 34:00.194
-DYLAN: And you think it's a...
-Of course.

34:01.957 --> 34:03.117
Put you on the record?

34:05.419 --> 34:06.408
On the record?

34:07.046 --> 34:09.287
You're the last person
to see Marjorie alive.

34:09.757 --> 34:11.873
The police are saying one thing,
you're saying another.

34:13.427 --> 34:14.337
I'm sorry...

34:14.345 --> 34:15.710
Are you asking if you can
interview me?

34:15.721 --> 34:16.631
Sarah, listen to me.

34:16.639 --> 34:18.800
There's something going on here.
And it's all tied back to Ariel.

34:18.807 --> 34:21.139
Now, if one person reads this
and remembers something,

34:21.143 --> 34:22.428
the night that Ariel went missing,

34:22.436 --> 34:23.425
we could crack this case.

34:23.604 --> 34:25.720
Dylan, a woman I saw
this afternoon

34:25.731 --> 34:27.392
is lying dead in a motel room

34:27.399 --> 34:28.935
because Cam and I
got too close to something.

34:28.943 --> 34:30.308
That's my point.

34:31.403 --> 34:34.315
And instead of asking if I'm okay,
you ask if you can interview me.

34:34.323 --> 34:35.108
Fine!

34:35.282 --> 34:36.192
Fine!

34:36.200 --> 34:36.985
No interview.

34:37.326 --> 34:38.907
How insensitive of me
to try to help you find

34:38.911 --> 34:39.741
a missing girl, right?

34:39.912 --> 34:41.322
Oh, great!
Now I'm the bad guy.

34:41.539 --> 34:42.824
You're classic.

34:44.333 --> 34:45.698
[ Running water]

35:11.652 --> 35:12.516
[Car braking ]

35:16.991 --> 35:19.027
What the hell are you doing
out here all alone?

35:19.326 --> 35:20.156
This time of night?

35:20.744 --> 35:21.824
Just getting some air.

35:22.162 --> 35:23.538
Come on.

35:25.749 --> 35:26.829
I insist. Get in.

35:29.503 --> 35:30.834
Fine.

35:36.594 --> 35:38.175
Sorry my stuff's in the front.

35:38.596 --> 35:41.087
You, uh... mind jumping
in the back?

35:44.435 --> 35:45.424
[ Opens door ]

35:48.314 --> 35:49.099
[ Closes door ]

35:51.358 --> 35:52.518
[ Engine starts ]

35:59.950 --> 36:01.906
VAUGHN: So what were you doing
out there?

36:02.870 --> 36:04.406
I don't know.

36:06.248 --> 36:10.241
You and Cam,
your optimism is admirable.

36:11.420 --> 36:14.207
Ariel's been missing
for a few years now.

36:15.257 --> 36:17.589
This isn't the first time
I've had to tell you, Sarah.

36:17.593 --> 36:18.799
This is police business, I know.

36:20.804 --> 36:23.341
So please, just let it go.
All right?

36:26.310 --> 36:27.425
Can I be blunt?

36:28.687 --> 36:32.271
Oh, I think you and I
are well past blunt.

36:32.650 --> 36:34.811
This entire investigation
is based on lies.

36:35.194 --> 36:37.435
Alison Sutherland lied,
Marjorie Travers.

36:39.239 --> 36:42.402
So, what, you think
this is some big conspiracy?

36:42.993 --> 36:44.449
Connect the dots.

36:44.828 --> 36:46.329
I tell you what.

36:47.081 --> 36:49.117
Why don't you connect them
for me?

36:51.460 --> 36:52.825
Okay.

36:55.714 --> 36:57.921
Ariel Peterson walked home
from a party.

36:58.342 --> 36:59.673
By herself.

37:00.511 --> 37:01.876
She gets into a car
on Chariton Street,

37:01.887 --> 37:03.878
and that's the last time
anyone ever saw her.

37:04.264 --> 37:06.175
SARAH: Those are the facts.

37:06.767 --> 37:07.552
Okay.

37:08.185 --> 37:09.595
Now for the lies.

37:10.813 --> 37:13.555
Alison Sutherland hacks
into Benny Peterson's account

37:13.565 --> 37:15.692
and writes fake
but incriminating e-mails

37:15.693 --> 37:18.059
that make it look like
he murdered his daughter.

37:18.779 --> 37:19.564
Then".

37:19.822 --> 37:21.904
Marjorie Travers corroborates
those e-mails

37:22.074 --> 37:24.315
by flat out lying
about where Ariel Peterson

37:24.326 --> 37:25.076
was that night.

37:26.078 --> 37:29.070
And then, today, Marjorie Travers
conveniently overdoses.

37:29.248 --> 37:32.115
Now, I'm not the police,
obviously, but...

37:33.419 --> 37:34.499
You know?

37:34.753 --> 37:37.165
It sounds to me like someone
got to Marjorie first.

37:40.342 --> 37:43.379
Nasty women really pull the wool
over your eyes.

37:44.847 --> 37:47.088
That's really easy to say
in hindsight.

37:47.099 --> 37:49.465
Oh, yeah, because cops
never pick or choose evidence

37:49.476 --> 37:50.727
to build a case.

37:51.061 --> 37:52.892
You know, this has worked out
really well for you.

37:53.230 --> 37:55.437
Alison and Marjorie are dead,
and you...

38:01.488 --> 38:03.945
I, what, Sarah?

38:18.589 --> 38:20.125
Now it's time for me to be blunt.

38:22.176 --> 38:23.382
You're an idiot.

38:25.137 --> 38:27.002
Not your hypothesis.

38:27.014 --> 38:27.878
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, no.

38:28.682 --> 38:30.013
You're dead on.

38:31.643 --> 38:33.804
You're an idiot
for getting in this car.

38:36.148 --> 38:37.558
Ah, ah, ah, ah, ah.

38:41.945 --> 38:43.685
Take your cell phone...

38:44.573 --> 38:46.609
and drop it out the window.

38:49.161 --> 38:51.527
[ Crickets chirping ]

38:51.997 --> 38:52.782
[ Inhales ]

38:52.998 --> 38:54.499
Do it.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.706
Now!

39:00.172 --> 39:01.708
[ Cell phone hitting the ground ]

39:02.716 --> 39:04.377
That's a good girl.

39:21.151 --> 39:22.482
[ Whistling ]

39:22.778 --> 39:24.564
SARAH: Where are you taking me?

39:25.030 --> 39:26.770
[ Continues whistling ]

39:27.533 --> 39:29.148
What if someone saw me
get into your car?

39:29.409 --> 39:30.865
I gave you a ride home.

39:31.203 --> 39:34.366
I dropped you off,
I saw you walk in,

39:34.373 --> 39:36.659
close the door, lock it.

39:37.543 --> 39:41.377
I had no idea The Executioner
was inside waiting for you.

39:42.673 --> 39:45.710
You know the punishment
for lust

39:46.051 --> 39:48.793
is being smothered in fire
and brimstone?

39:49.680 --> 39:51.341
But what's the punishment...

39:51.974 --> 39:53.180
for pride?

39:55.519 --> 39:56.759
Come on now, Sarah.

39:57.688 --> 39:59.178
It's not like you
to get tongue tied.

40:01.149 --> 40:02.605
What's the punishment?

40:03.986 --> 40:06.853
-Being broken on the wheel.
-On the wheel, yeah.

40:08.824 --> 40:11.156
Coming back to the town your parents
were murdered in,

40:11.743 --> 40:13.574
moving into the same house,

40:14.288 --> 40:17.246
trying to outsmart the police,
going toe to toe with a killer...

40:19.293 --> 40:21.124
That sounds like pride to me,
Sarah.

40:22.588 --> 40:23.748
No.

40:24.506 --> 40:26.713
No, it's not Executioner's MO.

40:27.467 --> 40:29.458
Well, I really don't give a shit.

40:32.014 --> 40:33.424
I'm the chief investigator.

40:33.724 --> 40:34.804
[ Chuckles ]

40:35.142 --> 40:37.508
-Cam will--
-Cam will nothing.

40:39.146 --> 40:40.431
Cam's my bitch.

40:56.580 --> 40:58.741
[Car bell clinging ]

41:01.418 --> 41:03.909
[ Whistling ]

41:10.552 --> 41:11.632
-Come on.
-SARAH: No!

41:11.637 --> 41:13.844
-S
hut up! Shut up'
-No! I

41:14.222 --> 41:15.132
God!

41:16.016 --> 41:17.597
-Shut up! Shut up!
-[ Screaming ]

41:17.851 --> 41:20.263
Or I will punch every tooth
out of your mouth.

41:20.437 --> 41:21.222
No!

41:24.107 --> 41:24.971
[ Screaming ]
No!

41:25.817 --> 41:27.068
No! Help!

41:27.486 --> 41:28.896
[ Whimpering ]

41:29.446 --> 41:30.481
[ Groans]

41:34.785 --> 41:36.195
[ Cracking noise ]
[ Screaming ]

41:37.996 --> 41:38.985
I was not...

41:39.456 --> 41:40.616
...a murderer, Sarah!

41:41.667 --> 41:42.577
No!

41:42.584 --> 41:43.869
Not until you made me one!

41:43.877 --> 41:44.957
[ Screaming ]

41:45.212 --> 41:46.702
Shu-- shut up!

41:46.880 --> 41:47.710
[ Continues screaming ]

41:47.923 --> 41:48.708
-Shut up.
-No!

41:49.007 --> 41:49.792
No!

41:50.133 --> 41:50.997
Shut up! Shut up.

41:51.385 --> 41:52.465
[Vaughn screaming ]

42:01.186 --> 42:01.971
[ Gunshot ]

42:04.314 --> 42:05.770
Sarah!

42:06.942 --> 42:08.648
VAUGHN: There's
nowhere to run, Sarah!

42:09.528 --> 42:10.392
[ Gunshot ]

42:10.404 --> 42:11.610
You hear me?

42:11.780 --> 42:12.986
You're not gonna get away!

42:14.700 --> 42:15.610
[ Gunshot ]

42:15.617 --> 42:17.357
Sarah!
[ Gunshot ]

42:18.078 --> 42:19.318
Sarah!

42:19.997 --> 42:21.157
Stop! Stop! Please! Please!

42:21.540 --> 42:22.950
Stop! Help me!
Stop! Please!

42:23.208 --> 42:24.323
Stop! Stop!

42:24.835 --> 42:25.790
What the hell are you doing?

42:26.044 --> 42:27.250
Help me, please!
He's trying to kill me!

42:27.587 --> 42:28.793
-[ Gunshot]
-[ Screaming ]

42:29.006 --> 42:30.212
-[ Gunshot ]
-WOMAN: Get in! Hurry!

42:31.174 --> 42:31.959
Who is he?

42:32.217 --> 42:33.002
[ Gunshot ]

42:42.144 --> 42:44.931
[Yelling ]
Fuck!

42:47.649 --> 42:49.185
[ Heart rate monitor beeping ]

42:53.405 --> 42:54.895
[ Coughs]
He said...

42:55.365 --> 42:58.072
He wasn't a murderer
until I turned him into someone.

42:58.368 --> 42:59.528
Or something... I don't know.
Just...

42:59.870 --> 43:01.531
No, Sarah.

43:01.705 --> 43:03.536
That-- that might actually be
a good thing.

43:04.124 --> 43:06.331
It might mean that...
that Ariel isn't dead.

43:06.334 --> 43:07.744
Maybe he didn't kill her
when he snatched her up.

43:07.753 --> 43:09.414
He will now.

43:09.629 --> 43:11.290
He was... he's desperate.

43:11.840 --> 43:13.796
[ Heart rate monitor beeping ]
[ Hospital PA chatter ]

43:14.926 --> 43:16.541
Sarah, I need to go.

43:16.803 --> 43:17.883
No.
[ Chuckles ]

43:17.888 --> 43:18.798
No, no, no.

43:19.097 --> 43:21.588
Look, I have cops
all over this hospital.

43:21.933 --> 43:23.059
Cam.
[ Sniffles ]

43:23.602 --> 43:25.308
Please. Please don't leave me.

43:29.357 --> 43:30.858
Okay.

43:32.444 --> 43:34.059
I promise you.

43:34.362 --> 43:37.900
That bastard will never get
within five feet of you again.

43:38.950 --> 43:40.360
Do you hear me?

43:40.869 --> 43:41.699
[ Sobbing ]

43:53.632 --> 43:55.338
Ariel, wake up.

43:56.009 --> 43:58.466
What? Why? What time is it?

44:00.388 --> 44:01.889
I'm sorry.

44:05.060 --> 44:06.140
Jake.

44:07.938 --> 44:09.474
ARIEL: Please let us go.

44:10.357 --> 44:11.563
No!

44:11.858 --> 44:14.110
Iain, please, just let us go!

44:14.528 --> 44:15.688
Iain!

44:15.862 --> 44:18.319
Just let us go,
and we won't tell anyone!

44:18.657 --> 44:19.988
We'll never tell anyone!

44:20.158 --> 44:21.022
Please, Iain!

44:21.243 --> 44:22.949
They already know!

44:24.412 --> 44:25.868
[ Panting ]

44:26.289 --> 44:27.790
The punishment for lust...

44:28.125 --> 44:29.615
is fire and brimstone.

44:29.626 --> 44:31.742
It's fire and brimstone,
and being burned alive!

44:32.337 --> 44:33.668
What are you talking about?

44:34.881 --> 44:36.087
Ariel, I've sinned.

44:36.341 --> 44:37.626
I've sinned...

44:38.301 --> 44:40.087
I have to pay
for what I've done!

44:41.888 --> 44:42.673
ARIEL: No!

44:42.848 --> 44:44.384
Please, Iain!
Iain, Iain, Iain!

44:44.850 --> 44:46.465
Iain, listen!

44:46.935 --> 44:48.220
Listen, I can die, okay?

44:48.395 --> 44:49.180
I'm ready.

44:49.437 --> 44:50.222
We can die together.

44:50.772 --> 44:53.354
But Jake's just a little kid!
He's just a little kid!

44:53.942 --> 44:55.057
Please! Iain!

44:55.443 --> 44:56.774
[ Sobbing ]

44:57.237 --> 44:58.272
[ Screams ]

45:13.461 --> 45:14.246
Iain!

45:15.130 --> 45:16.290
It's Cam!

45:16.756 --> 45:18.292
We need to talk.

45:18.592 --> 45:20.048
Open up!

45:20.051 --> 45:21.632
[ Door unlocking ]

45:23.889 --> 45:24.674
Cam!

45:25.098 --> 45:27.339
Is everything okay?
Did something happen?

45:28.059 --> 45:29.924
Nancy, you need to tell us
where your husband is.

45:30.478 --> 45:31.263
Now!

45:31.688 --> 45:34.304
I-- I don't like your tone,
Cameron.

45:34.983 --> 45:36.063
You don't like my tone?

45:36.359 --> 45:37.269
Nancy...

45:37.569 --> 45:39.605
You don't like my tone, then
answer my goddamn question!

45:39.613 --> 45:40.693
Where's your husband?

45:41.406 --> 45:42.486
Cam!

45:44.784 --> 45:45.910
Nancy.

45:46.077 --> 45:48.204
Hi Nancy, I'm Sarah.

45:48.788 --> 45:51.951
Sorry, everyone's
just a little bit on edge.

45:52.334 --> 45:53.540
We need your help, okay?

45:53.835 --> 45:55.075
There's-- there's a girl in danger.

45:55.754 --> 45:58.040
Because of Iain?
That's ridiculous.

45:58.048 --> 45:59.584
-I'm sorry, Iain's not like that.
-No, no, no.

45:59.883 --> 46:00.668
Of course not.

46:01.384 --> 46:04.592
In fact, we think he might be
protecting her, we just...

46:05.180 --> 46:06.886
just need to know
where they are.

46:09.476 --> 46:11.307
Iain's business
is his own business.

46:11.645 --> 46:12.930
Yeah, no, I know but...

46:12.938 --> 46:15.224
This is so important, Nancy.

46:19.569 --> 46:22.936
Do you ever watch
those home shows on TV?

46:23.448 --> 46:25.313
You know, the ones
where the wives get to design

46:25.325 --> 46:27.065
their new house,
and their husbands...

46:27.369 --> 46:29.109
Well, the husbands
get something called a...

46:29.871 --> 46:31.202
a man cave.

46:31.831 --> 46:33.913
Isn't that a hoot?
A man cave?

46:34.167 --> 46:34.952
[ Snickers ]

46:35.252 --> 46:36.492
You know, a place where...

46:36.795 --> 46:38.786
boys can be boys,
no girls allowed.

46:40.048 --> 46:42.414
Yeah, yeah. Well...

46:43.260 --> 46:45.501
Does Iain... have a man cave?

46:45.845 --> 46:47.096
Yes.

46:48.473 --> 46:51.010
But I don't go there
because I'm not allowed.

46:52.894 --> 46:55.180
We just want to help him,
Nancy.

47:00.402 --> 47:02.233
Vaughn?

47:02.445 --> 47:04.231
It's Cam.
Come on out.

47:04.656 --> 47:06.442
We've got you surrounded.

47:09.077 --> 47:11.033
[ Panting ]

47:13.415 --> 47:15.576
CAM: Ariel?

47:28.096 --> 47:29.461
[ Engine running ]

47:29.723 --> 47:30.553
[ Sobbing ]

47:31.474 --> 47:32.759
You can let go, Ariel.

47:33.101 --> 47:34.557
PARAMEDIC:
Your son will be okay.

47:34.811 --> 47:36.267
I'm just going to examine him.

47:36.855 --> 47:38.015
He's safe now.

47:40.400 --> 47:42.106
[ Engine running ]

47:42.444 --> 47:43.229
[ Sighs ]

47:43.570 --> 47:44.400
[ Sniffles ]

47:52.287 --> 47:53.618
Ariel?

47:54.247 --> 47:55.362
-HEA THER: You...
-Mom.

47:56.249 --> 47:57.079
[ Sobbing ]

48:02.255 --> 48:03.620
I love you!

48:03.882 --> 48:04.917
[ Continued sobbing ]

48:13.933 --> 48:15.139
Mom!

48:20.982 --> 48:22.722
[ Wind rustling ]

48:35.080 --> 48:36.115
TOM: Sarah.

48:37.165 --> 48:38.075
-Hey.
-[ Groans]

48:38.291 --> 48:40.202
Take it easy.
Take it easy!

48:42.962 --> 48:44.748
Did they call you?

48:45.548 --> 48:46.924
SARAH: No.

48:47.092 --> 48:48.207
I came myself.

48:48.426 --> 48:49.211
[ Tom sighs ]

48:51.513 --> 48:52.969
SARAH: How you feeling?

48:53.181 --> 48:54.546
[ Chuckles ]

48:54.557 --> 48:56.263
How am I feeling?

48:56.476 --> 48:58.091
[ Inhales deeply ]

48:59.020 --> 49:00.226
You came to see me.

49:02.649 --> 49:04.139
Yeah.

49:05.235 --> 49:07.476
Had a lot of time to think.

49:07.487 --> 49:09.478
Put things into perspective and...

49:10.949 --> 49:11.938
What?

49:13.910 --> 49:17.073
I don't have enough family left
to pick and choose. So...

49:18.164 --> 49:19.995
SARAH: If we're gonna do this...

49:20.959 --> 49:22.244
there's gonna be
some ground rules.

49:22.752 --> 49:24.162
Anything.

49:28.133 --> 49:29.919
No more lies.

49:32.429 --> 49:34.385
No more lies.

49:37.058 --> 49:38.798
I promise.

49:40.353 --> 49:42.093
What do you want to know?

49:44.190 --> 49:46.351
I want to know why you killed my...

49:48.278 --> 49:50.564
my mother and her husband.

49:53.533 --> 49:55.990
I want you to tell me the truth.

49:56.244 --> 49:58.826
I want you to tell me everything.

49:59.289 --> 50:00.745
Every detail.

50:01.332 --> 50:02.788
From the beginning.

50:06.045 --> 50:08.627
[ Inhales deeply ]

50:10.008 --> 50:11.794
[ Engine running ]

50:12.385 --> 50:14.296
[ Panting ]

50:16.264 --> 50:17.925
[ Groans]

50:20.477 --> 50:22.013
[ Groans]

51:18.284 --> 51:19.239
[ Groans]

51:25.041 --> 51:26.781
[ Metal door closing ]

51:36.886 --> 51:37.671
No.

51:54.946 --> 51:55.731
[ Inaudible ]

51:58.241 --> 51:59.230
Help! Help!

51:59.867 --> 52:00.902
Oh, no!

52:02.620 --> 52:05.157
Somebody, help me!

52:06.165 --> 52:07.371
Help me!

52:07.625 --> 52:08.831
Someone, help me!

52:10.169 --> 52:11.579
[ Screaming ]

52:12.130 --> 52:13.666
VAUGHN: Help me!

52:14.173 --> 52:15.208
Help me!

52:15.883 --> 52:17.214
[ Screaming ]

52:17.427 --> 52:18.507
No!

52:19.554 --> 52:20.794
Somebody...

52:20.805 --> 52:22.591
...help me!

52:23.099 --> 52:24.384
[ Screaming ]

52:28.855 --> 52:31.346
[ Continued screaming ]

52:33.610 --> 52:34.395
Help me!
